en_583848_0	Troops of the 1 Vijayabahu Infantry Regiment (VIR) under command to the 52 Division and 521 Brigade of the Security Force Headquarters - Jaffna (SFHQ-J) extending their community projects renovated lavatories of Madihe Pannaseeha Vidyalaya, Puttur, during the school vacation and handed over to the school authorities on Monday (3).
en_583848_1	The renovation work was carried out under the guidance of Commander, Security Forces - Jaffna (SF-J), Major General Darshana Hettiarachchi.
en_583848_2	The renovation was funded by Dharma Vijaya Foundation at Colombo 7.
en_583848_3	The renovation work was begun to coincide with the 30th anniversary of the 1 VIR serving under the SFHQ-J.
en_583848_4	Commanding Officer, Lieutenant Colonel Dammika Jayarathne, Education Director, Kopai and Principal were also there at the time of the formal handover.
